# Deep Sea — game architecture and TDD

## Where logic lives

- **Gameplay and simulation** belong in `src/game/`. Do not put tower defense rules, waves, economy, or combat in Three.js setup, React, or ad-hoc scripts unless they are thin adapters that call `src/game`.
- **Docs/schema** in `docs/map-schema.md` are the source of truth for map JSON; keep `map-types.ts` / `types.ts` aligned when the schema changes.

## Module responsibilities (respect boundaries)

| Area | Use |
|------|-----|
| `MapController` | Static layout, paths, build slots, **mutable** placed defenses list |
| `EconomyController` | Shells, earn vs refund, lifetime earned |
| `CastleController` | Citadel HP |
| `EnemyController` | One enemy — path progress, movement, HP |
| `DefenseController` | One tower snapshot — upgrades, Arc Spine chain math |
| `WaveDirector` | Prep/active wave time budgets, spawn pacing per group |
| `spawnEnemyFromWaveGroup` | Map + wave group → `EnemyController` |
| `TargetingSystem` | `targetMode` selection only |
| `DamageResolver` | One attack resolution (incl. chains), kill loot |
| `GameSession` | **Single orchestration** — `tick` order: waves → enemies/movement/leaks → tower fire → wave advance |

- Add **new systems** as focused modules under `src/game/` and **wire them from `GameSession`** (or another clear orchestrator), not by scattering timers across the codebase.
- **Exports**: add public API to `src/game/index.ts` when introducing new user-facing types or classes.

## Testing (TDD preferred)

- **Default workflow:** when adding or changing behavior, write or update a **Vitest** test first when practical (red → green → refactor). Run `npm test` before finishing.
- Tests live in `tests/**/*.test.ts`; exercise **headless** `src/game` code without requiring WebGL.
- Prefer **fast unit tests** on pure helpers and controllers; use **small fixtures** or `data/maps/*.json` where integration adds value.
- **White-box tests** may use a typed test-only interface and `as unknown as …` to call `private` methods (see existing tests); if you change private helpers, update those tests.

## Anti-patterns

- Duplicating wave timing, targeting, or damage rules outside `WaveDirector` / `TargetingSystem` / `DamageResolver`.
- `GameSession.tick` order forks (e.g. towers firing before movement) without a deliberate, documented reason.
- Magic numbers for balance scattered everywhere — prefer named constants (e.g. `enemy-stats.ts`, tuning near `DamageResolver`) and tests that lock intended behavior.
